description: {"blocks":[{"key":"8dir6","text":"Assessing the capacity of IL-15 analogs (e.g. within TriKE molecules) to stimulate proliferation of NK-92 cells. NK-92 are deprived of cytokines overnight, then cultured with IL-15 analogs for two days. After this time, the expansion of viable cells is quantitatively assessed using a redox-sensitive dye that changes from blue/non-fluorescent in media to pink/fluorescent upon reduction in viable cells. {"blocks":[{"key":"6juuj","text":"NK-92 culture conditions: ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ausq1","text":"Humidified incubator at 37.0°C, 5% CO2","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":37,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"26gvo","text":"Culture conditions:  Replace medium every 2 ‐ 3 days","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1ljba","text":"Passage interval:  Passage 2 ‐ 3 times a week","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"64hvj","text":"Sub-cultivation ratio: 1:2 - 1:3","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1lce8","text":"Seeding conditions: 2x105 - 3x105 cells/mL","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":24,"length":1},{"style":"sup","offset":32,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"g5pn","text":"NK-92 freezing protocol:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7gc5m","text":"Freeze medium: 50% FBS; 40% NK92 media; 10% DMSO","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cc20n","text":"Freeze no more than 5x106 cells/mL ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":24,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"69hed","text":"Storage temperature: liquid nitrogen vapor phase","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2qtbo","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ablaq","text":"Deprive NK-92 of IL-2 at least 16 h prior to plating cells.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4smu6","text":"Dilute all drugs in media (without IL-2) to 5x the highest concentration to be tested (e.g. 150 nM). This will be used to make a serial dilution of the drug (3x, 5x or 10x depending on range required).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4t5vm","text":"Plate NK-92 in triplicate into a 96 well black assay plate at 5 x 104 cells/well in 80 μL of media without IL-2. Avoid using the wells at the edge of the plate at these undergo the greatest evaporation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":68,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cbl4d","text":"Add 20 μL of diluted drug to each well containing NK-92. Include a no drug condition as a negative control.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bpaat","text":"Count NK cells (at least 4.8 million will be required for a full plate).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"dbhvh","text":"Spin NK-92 at 1600 RPM for 5 min and remove the supernatant.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"2fo1r","text":"Spin NK-92 at 1600 RPM for 5 min and remove supernatant. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4bs1e","text":"Resuspend cells at 7.5 x 105cells/mL in media without IL-2 and return to the incubator overnight.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":27,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2agn5","text":"After 24 h, add 10 µL resazurin to each well, mix and incubate for 1 h at 37℃ and 5% CO2.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"aq0go","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"3v405","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"reagents","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"id":404579,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Resazurin","linfor":"","url":"https://www.rndsystems.com/products/resazurin_ar002","sku":"AR002","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":1,"can_edit":0,"guid":"560AFCB08EEF11EAAB009FFA15440066","in_steps":null,"vendor":{"id":236,"name":"R\u0026D Systems","link":"http://www.rndsystems.com","image":{"source":"/img/vendors/placeholder.png","placeholder":"/img/vendors/placeholder.png"}}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"51oup","text":"Replace the plate in the incubator and wait 1 h before repeating step 7. Repeat this process to obtain four readings in total. Select the most stable readings for analysis (usually 3 h).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"crstv","text":"Analyze the adjusted readings using Graphpad Prism. Log transform the data and calculate a non-linear fit using \"log(agonist) vs. normalized response -- Variable slope - Least squares fit\" in order to obtain an EC 50.
